    "ailments_description": "The most common ailments you can heal with Souroubea lepidota are fever and rheumatism. Souroubea lepidota is traditionally used to treat malaria, a disease caused by Plasmodium parasites, which affects millions of people worldwide. Additionally, studies have shown that extracts from Souroubea lepidota exhibit anti-inflammatory properties, making it an effective remedy for treating rheumatoid arthritis. Furthermore, Souroubea lepidota has been found to possess antimicrobial properties, which can help alleviate skin infections, such as eczema, and other dermatological conditions. In some regions, Souroubea lepidota is also used to treat respiratory issues, including bronchitis.",
