    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Souroubea lepidota are alkaloids such as lepidotine, lepidotinone, and lepidotinine, which have been shown to possess anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial properties. The plant also contains flavonoids like quercetin and kaempferol, which are known for their antioxidant and anti-inflammatory activities. In addition, the presence of phenolic acids, including ferulic acid and caffeic acid, has been reported, contributing to the plant's antimicrobial and anti-cancer properties. The sesquiterpene lactone, lepidoside, has also been identified, exhibiting anti-inflammatory and immunosuppressive effects. These constituents are responsible for the plant's potential therapeutic applications in treating various diseases, including inflammation, infections, and cancer.",
